\begin_layout Standard
The ball walk does not mix rapidly from all starting points in arbitrary convex bodies.
 While this hurdle can be overcome by starting with a deep point and carefully maintaining a warm start,
 it is natural to ask if there is a simple process that does truly mix rapidly from any starting point.
 Hit-and-Run satisfies this requirement.
