\begin_layout Lemma
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "lem:SSC-KLS"

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{n}$
\end_inset

 be the KLS constant of isotropic logconcave densities in 
\begin_inset Formula $\R^{n}$
\end_inset

,
 namely,
 for any isotropic logconcave density 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 and any set 
\begin_inset Formula $S\subset\Rn$
\end_inset

,
 we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int_{\partial S}p(x)dx\geq\frac{1}{\psi_{n}}\min\left\{ \int_{S}p(x)dx,\int_{\R^{n}\backslash S}p(x)dx\right\} .
\]

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\mh(x)$
\end_inset

 be the Hessian of the universal or entropic barriers.
 Then,
 we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\norm{\mathbf{H}(x)^{-1/2}D\mathbf{H}(x)[h]\mathbf{H}(x)^{-1/2}}_{F}=O(\psi_{n})\norm h_{x}.
\]

\end_inset

In short,
 the universal and entropic barriers in 
\begin_inset Formula $\R^{n}$
\end_inset

 are strongly self-concordant up to a scaling factor depending on 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{n}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In fact,
 the proof shows that up to a logarithmic factor the strong self-concordance of these barriers is 
\emph on
equivalent 
\emph default
to the KLS conjecture.
